President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Thomas Hart Armbruster as Ambassador to the Republic of the Marshall Islands and David Bruce Wharton as Ambassador to the Republic of Zimbabwe, both in the Department of State. He also intends to appoint William J. Shaw as a member of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom. Armbruster is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as a Diplomat-in-Residence at City College in New York. Wharton is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and is currently Deputy Assistant Secretary for Public Diplomacy in the Bureau of African Affairs at the Department of State. Shaw is a Reverend and has served as Pastor of the White Rock Baptist Church in Philadelphia since 1956. He is also a member of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom.